            <div type="translation">
            <p>Malkû, son of Moqîmû. Alas! (Legrain 1927: 348)</p></div>

            <div type="commentary">
            <p>For the names Malkû and Moqîmû--both common in Palmyra--see J. K. Stark, Personal
                    Names in Palmyrene Inscriptions (Oxford 1971), pp. 95-96. The deceased are
                    probably servants, as suggested by the small size of their figures.</p></div>
            

